<task id="063" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.I4 — Spe.Integration.Tests WireMock fixture updates (wiremock-drift category)</title>
    <status>completed-merged-with-062</status>
    <completed-date>2026-05-31</completed-date>
    <completion-summary>
      MERGED INTO TASK 062 per task 024 triage recommendation (both tasks edit the same file
      tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/IntegrationTestFixture.cs — anti-parallelism risk
      analogous to NFR-07 CustomWebAppFactory.cs §4.5). Single agent ran 062+063 together.

      Scope handled by merged 062:
      - Cluster B (SpeAdmin:KeyVaultUri, 98 projected): KEY ALREADY PRESENT in
        IntegrationTestFixture.cs line 74 (added by upstream commit 1b5cf735 — Reporting Wave 6).
        No edit needed in this fixture.
      - Cluster C (Reporting Skip path, 3 projected): CLEARED transitively by the Cosmos
        config fix in 062. All 3 GetStatus_ReturnsCorrectPrivilegeLevel_PerRole rows now Pass.
        No skip-tagging needed; no flaky-quarantine entry required.

      Residual 98 active SpeAdmin:KeyVaultUri errors in the post-062 TRX come from 8 SIBLING
      fixtures (KnowledgeBaseTestFixture, SemanticSearchTestFixture, etc.) that inherit
      WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt; directly — OUTSIDE the IntegrationTestFixture.cs scope
      of tasks 062 + 063. See notes/handoffs/integration-fixture-sibling-discovery-2026-05-31.md
      for the sibling-fixture follow-up scoping handoff.

      WireMock JSON fixtures (the original framing of task 063): no wiremock-drift category
      surfaced in task 024 triage — the actual cluster was "fixture-config-drift" satisfied
      by config dict edits, not WireMock JSON updates. No WireMock JSON files modified.

      See merged completion summary in task 062.
    </completion-summary>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, integration-tier, p23-i, integration-test, spe, wiremock, testing</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-I</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>WireMock JSON fixture files under tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/Fixtures/ are disjoint from .cs source repaired in task 062; also disjoint from BFF Integration batches (060/061)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update WireMock JSON fixture files in `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/Fixtures/`
    (or equivalent location per project structure) per the wiremock-drift category in the Phase 1
    integration-test triage (`projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md`).
    Per design.md §7 Phase 2+3 section: WireMock fixture updates are explicitly test-only changes
    permitted under NFR-01.

    For each fixture identified in the wiremock-drift category:
    1. Identify the Graph API endpoint stubbed by the fixture
    2. Compare the fixture's stubbed response against the current Graph SDK contract
       (response shape, headers, status codes)
    3. Update the JSON to match current contract
    4. Verify the consuming test now Passes
    5. Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` to consuming test class

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If a fixture file
    requires &gt;50% line replacement (more than half the JSON nodes change), HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-063-{FixtureName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every consuming test ends in `repaired`,
    `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior integration-test specialist with WireMock + Microsoft Graph contract expertise.</role>

  <goal>
    All WireMock fixture files identified in the Phase 1 triage as wiremock-drift are updated to
    match current Graph contract. Consuming tests Pass. §6.2 traits applied.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="triage">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/integration-test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation (applies to fixture JSON)</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every consuming test gets a §6.2 final end-state trait</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-18">All INTEGRATION-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="triage-scope">Only handle wiremock-drift category; compile/signature drift is task 062</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      WireMock fixtures stub Graph API responses for integration tests. When Graph SDK upgrades
      or Graph API contracts evolve, fixtures drift. Phase 1 task 024 categorizes which failures
      are wiremock-drift; this task updates those fixtures. Disjoint from task 062 (which handles
      compile/signature drift in .cs source).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="024" status="not-started">Spe.Integration.Tests baseline triage complete</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/Fixtures/*.json (those classified as wiremock-drift in triage)</file>
    <file>tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/**/*.json (any WireMock-format fixture)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `integration-test-triage.md` produced by task 024. Identify all WireMock fixtures classified as wiremock-drift.</step>
    <step order="2">For each fixture: identify the Graph endpoint stubbed (request URL pattern); identify the consuming test class(es).</step>
    <step order="3">Look up current Graph SDK contract for that endpoint (response shape, status codes, headers).</step>
    <step order="4">Compute pre-edit JSON node count per fixture. If any planned edit would exceed 50% of nodes → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-063-{FixtureName}.md`, await owner approval.</step>
    <step order="5">Update fixture JSON to match current contract. Preserve test data values where possible (change shape, not test semantics).</step>
    <step order="6">Apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` to consuming test class(es).</step>
    <step order="7">After each fixture update: `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~&lt;ConsumingClassName&gt;"` verify Pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with disposition (fixtures updated, consuming tests now Passing).</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (Spe.Integration.Tests project)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/Fixtures/*.json (WireMock fixtures, updated)</output>
    <output type="code">Consuming test classes (trait applied)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All wiremock-drift fixtures updated to current Graph contract; consuming tests Pass</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-fixture JSON diff &lt;50% node replacement (NFR-02)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every consuming test has a §6.2 final end-state trait</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No overlap with task 062 (.cs source files)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
